; eq-shape-band — axiom-1's two states are the value shape of every truth
; answer, three-way: a comparison or logic result IS the integer 0 or 1
; (states are 0/1/nothing), so it flows directly into arithmetic on all
; sibling kernels — the same shape the JIT's emitted C produces. No
; if-reduction stands between a question and its use; this verdict is
; itself composed of eq answers multiplied by bit weights.
;
; Verdict 255 when the shape holds:
;   1    eq feeds mul directly: (mul (eq 2 2) 5) is 5
;   2    the false state is 0, a value that multiplies: (mul (eq 1 2) 7) is 0
;   4    ordering answers add: (lt 1 2) + (gt 1 2) is 1
;   8    logic answers feed arithmetic: (mul (and (eq 1 1) (lt 0 1)) 7) is 7
;   16   not is the 0/1 flip: (not (eq 1 2)) + (not (eq 3 3)) is 1
;   32   the float path answers in the same two states: (mul (lt 1.5 2.5) 3) is 3
;   64   a bool literal carries its state into eq as 1/0: (eq (gt 3 2) true) is 1
;   128  an answer is the next question's operand: (eq 4 4) + (eq 4 5) is 1
(do
    (let c0 (mul (eq (mul (eq 2 2) 5) 5) 1))
    (let c1 (mul (eq (mul (eq 1 2) 7) 0) 2))
    (let c2 (mul (eq (add (lt 1 2) (gt 1 2)) 1) 4))
    (let c3 (mul (eq (mul (and (eq 1 1) (lt 0 1)) 7) 7) 8))
    (let c4 (mul (eq (add (not (eq 1 2)) (not (eq 3 3))) 1) 16))
    (let c5 (mul (eq (mul (lt 1.5 2.5) 3) 3) 32))
    (let c6 (mul (eq (gt 3 2) true) 64))
    (let c7 (mul (eq (add (eq 4 4) (eq 4 5)) 1) 128))
    (add c0 (add c1 (add c2 (add c3 (add c4 (add c5 (add c6 c7))))))))
